        </p>
        <p>
            Higher stress levels also appear to increase the risk of development of gadolinium-enhancing lesions. A recent randomized trial shows that reducing stress using stress management therapy (SMT), a cognitive-behavioural therapy approach, results in a statistically significant reduction in new magnetic resonance imaging lesions.<sup>48</sup>
